Orascom Construction Rises After Approving Share Buyback

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-07-20T09:24:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/orascom-construction-rises-after-approving-share-buyback.html
Orascom Construction Industries (OCIC) ,
Egypt’s biggest publicly traded builder, rose for the first time
in three days after its board of directors approved a share-
repurchase plan.  The shares of the Cairo-based company advanced 1.3 percent
to 269.98 Egyptian pounds at 10:51 a.m. in Cairo, valuing
Orascom Construction at 55.9 billion pounds ($9.4 billion). The
benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30)  added 0.5 percent.  Orascom’s board approved buying back about 675,000 shares
trading in Cairo or  London  from July 26 to Aug. 25, to support
the stock price. The company purchased 440,000 shares trading in
London last month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Dubai at 
